tle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 12:07:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=629.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Has Venril Sathir gotten harder over time?</span><hr size=1> Glad this came up, because I wanted to ask some very similar questions for you experienced VS hunters out there.<br><br>Saturday, we went in to get the stones for the Ranger/Druid epic for some of our guildies. I was MA (I'm a 55 warrior with nothing special for gear).  SA was also a 55. We didn't have many folks online so we went in with 11 people to give it a shot.<br>Warrior - Warrior - Cleric - Cleric - Chanter - Chanter - Druid - Druid - Ranger - Bard - Monk.<br>(All players in the 51 to 56 range. No real ubers.)<br><br>Buffed up in the staging area as for any large mob and I accompanied the ranger up for the turnin. I got aggro when VS spawned (triggered one, of course) then pulled him to center of room (with one summon first) and called in the troops. It went ok, with the exception of both chanters getting a HUGE lag spike dand my Rune chain failing. I got killed by the 1500 HP lifetaps before they could start again, but the SA picked up the load then and they finished him off and we got the epic pieces for our guildies. <br><br>First of all, that was a pretty straight forward attack. I'm the raid leader for our guild. Anything I cn do to fine tune the attack strategy?  Was eleven folks not enough at our level? (That was a CLOSE fight either way).  Should I just have more, or is that typical?<br><br>Next, how about the real VS? Peopl say he's much tougher. How so? More HP? Tap for more than 1500? GAWD I hope not!  AE's or something?<br><br>Any guidance appreciated. We have a bunch of rangers and druids who want this guy, so I'll need to do it several more times. <p>Jakugg Blackheart55 Troll Myrmidon, <Souls of Honour> Xev</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umikoobixieslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mikoo Bixieslayer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 12:30:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=629.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Has Venril Sathir gotten harder over time?</span><hr size=1> VSR is a much easier fight.  It is the same 1500pt lifetap but it seldom happens if at all when fighting VSR.  However the spawned VS constantly procs the 1500pt lifetap and allthough I am not sure, I believe he has more HP than VSR.<br><br>I would be very surprised that two groups sub 60 could take down the Real VS.  For one, I don't see how a 55 warrior could hold taunt let alone survive more than about 3 rounds of that lifetap. <p><HR><font color = "#000080" size = 2 face = "Arial"><B>Mikoo Bixieslayer</b><BR>Halfling Myrmidon<BR>Proud Officer of <br><a href=http://pub43.ezboard.com/bhereticsoftheapocalypse>Heretics of the Apocalypse</a><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12473>Profile</a></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhagusbruichladdich.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hagus Bruichladdich</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 172<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 1:48:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=629.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.divinelegion.com/images/Hagus_256color.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Has Venril Sathir gotten harder over time?</span><hr size=1> &quot;They fixed lifetap on npcs now a few weeks ago, so yes he got harder since he regens now &quot;<br><br>How so?  <br><br>Do the lifetaps ignore runes all together?  Example: 1500 lifetap, 500 rune.  1500 points of real damage, rune still on?<br><br>or<br><br>Do they take off the rune, the rune absorbing part of the damage?  Example: 1500 lifetap, 500 rune.  1000 points of real damage, rune used?<br><br>In any of the cases, is it &quot;just&quot; VS that does this now?  Or is it VS, VSR, Nortav, the AE lifetaps that Maestro and the Very Unpleasant Hand have?  (If all NPCs ignore runes now, I'd assume Maestro's AE lifetaps would make him 100x harder than he was before). <p>--Hagus Bruichladdich<BR><BR>"Tilt woon bock weth me dog!!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucoray.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Coray</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 2:38:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=629.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Has Venril Sathir gotten harder over time?</span><hr size=1> 2 groups probably couldn't kill him using what seems to be the general tactic people settled on, baring of course mana burn wizards, where 3 of them could easily kill him.<br><br>2 groups could still kill him though, just depends on how you do it.  if he doesn't lifetap anyone, then it isn't a factor. <p></p><i>