anter will be LoM, so all the healers present begin to use small, fast heals on the MT. If some fool off tank gets agro let them die, it's for the best. In fact not giving the off tanks HP buffs help, less for VS to tap (g'luck getting them to understand that tho...)<br><br>Now depending on how much damage dealing you have, the MT picks a spot and hits his ripo disc. At this point you have 9 seconds to kill him, give or take a couple. Wwhen the MT ripo's all the off tanks hit offensive discs, and all the burners open up. The healers continue small short heals to the MT in case VS lives through the assualt for a bit past ripo disc.<br><br>Hope you enjoy this, personally was much more fun for me to find out for myself (ahh the wonders of a camped out cleric, how easy it makes CR's).<br><br>Subb<br><br>EDIT- <br>PS debuffs = worthless, shammies just buff the MT and then chloroblast <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usubbiano.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Subbiano</A> at: 3/22/02 2:01:14 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showMessageRange?topicID=629.topic&start=21&stop=35>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showPrevMessage?topicID=629.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showNextMessage?topicID=629.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=629.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.emailToFriend?topicID=629.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/ema